b'' b'i just installed a new truetype font under ms-windows b'but though all the applications display the font correctly on the' b'screen, quite a few of them fail to print out the document correctly' b'(on a laserjet non-postscript printer).' b'...' b'but when i use the windows accessory write, the printer prints square' b'boxes in place of the characters of the new font. yet, write does' b'display the font correctly on the screen.' b'' b'this is a common problem with highly complex truetype fonts. microsoft' b'admits to a problem with older versions of the postscript printer driver,' b"but i've found it to be pretty generic." b'' b'you can get around the problem by adjusting the parameter outlinethreshold' b'in the [truetype] section of win.ini. this entry specifies the number of' b'pels-per-em at which windows will render truetype fonts as outline fonts' b"instead of as bitmap fonts. the default is i've generally been able" b'to get fonts to work by setting outlinethreshold=160. depending on your' b'printer resolution and the point size you are using, you may need a' b'different value.' b'' b'the windows resource kit warns against going above presumably, that' b"might cause fonts to print as square boxes or something. (i'm not" b'smiling.)' b'' b'--' b'bob nichols' b'at&t bell laboratories' 